The paper deals with privacy and utility tradeoffs, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of differential privacy (DP) is also a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and privacy-preserving data analysis (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the categorization of source distribution sets, which could fall under the sub-category of statistical learning theory (cs.SI).
